          • [ - ] ZuberiMamba - member since 11-Aug-16

            A well taken header by Benzema makes the difference in this classic matchup which surprisingly only one goal scored. The key player for Madrid in this game was, obviously, Ramos as he came back with a commanding presence after some calamitous defending their opening CL-game. Although the defence was much improved in terms of organisation and ferocity, the midfield still seemed incredibly porous with Casemiro having to do a lot of work covering up the attacking players. This seems to be a reoccurring issue for the serial CL-winners as they towards the end of last season and in the PSG-match were ran riot in midfield. It was a positive display from the Madrid wingers but Sevilla only lacked that lethal finish as their wingbacks (and Ocampos) consistently whipped in high-curling crosses (Navas also a standout-player). A much needed result for the joint-league leaders but not a convincing win by any stretch of the imagination.
